Citations
Date:  24/3/1969
Source:  Weekly News
Author:
Vol / Page:  45
Edition:
Quote:  The children went back to school after New Year till the cocksfoot seed was ripe, then were allowed holidays (about a fortnight..) to help to harvest it. The children just loved these 'grass-seed holidays' as they were called.
